  <section class="section">
    <h2>Why Checkpoints Matter</h2>

```
<p>
  Every poker decision creates movement. Some decisions move you forward. Some move you backward. Some protect you from damage. Some create future opportunities.
</p>

<p>
  The checkpoint idea forces you to slow down just enough to recognize what kind of decision you are really making.
</p>

<p>
  Are you entering a hand with a purpose? Are you calling because the price is right or because you are curious? Are you betting for value, pressure, protection, or confusion? Are you risking chips because the spot deserves it, or because emotion has taken over?
</p>

<p>
  These questions matter because poker punishes unclear thinking.
</p>

<div class="highlight">
  The Core System gives you a repeatable way to bring your mind back to the decision instead of the emotion.
</div>
```

